The paper discusses signal edge-preserving smoothing filters, which are commonly used in computer vision and graphics applications. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.GR (Graphics) are the most likely categories. The paper also mentions numerical experiments, which suggests that it may belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper deals with optimization methods, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory).
